00:06:29.920 --> 00:06:34.130
Okay. So I wanted to talk
a little about our goals

00:06:34.130 --> 00:06:37.120
because they feed directly into
why we did this event this week.

00:06:37.120 --> 00:06:39.970
It's difficult for me -- wait.

00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:43.700
So the first one is enable
transformational experiences

00:06:43.700 --> 00:06:46.090
by connecting users
with the Library

00:06:46.090 --> 00:06:47.720
and its digital collections.

00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:51.330
So some people, people
ask us all the time,

00:06:51.330 --> 00:06:53.020
how do you measure impact?

00:06:53.020 --> 00:06:56.780
And the way that we think about
it is if you see a photograph,

00:06:56.780 --> 00:06:59.680
for example, whether it's
a dataset or a single item,

00:06:59.680 --> 00:07:02.710
and it transforms the way that
you think about American history

00:07:02.710 --> 00:07:05.170
and culture, then
we've done our job.

00:07:05.170 --> 00:07:09.750
So that was partly the impetus
for the flash build this week.

00:07:09.750 --> 00:07:14.480
And then our second big
goal is to prototype ideas

00:07:14.480 --> 00:07:16.520
and build relationship
with stakeholders

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:18.910
that will realize the
Library's digital strategy.

00:07:18.910 --> 00:07:22.280
So you heard from Kate earlier
we're launching a digital

00:07:22.280 --> 00:07:26.730
strategy, a new digital
strategy, and it's Lab's job

00:07:26.730 --> 00:07:31.260
to pilot some of those ideas in
small safe ways to see whether

00:07:31.260 --> 00:07:34.100
or not they work for the Library
of Congress's environment.

00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:39.580
And then the last goal is
to strengthen our community

00:07:39.580 --> 00:07:42.090
by sharing our work for
transparency, feedback,

00:07:42.090 --> 00:07:43.390
and knowledge exchange.

00:07:43.390 --> 00:07:46.000
So that's what we're doing
now in a very extreme sense

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:49.520
because we're going to
demo something for you live

00:07:49.520 --> 00:07:51.490
that no one has ever
seen before.

