that was made by Laura Wrubel,

00:12:24.240 --> 00:12:25.830
who was a Software
Development Librarian

00:12:25.830 --> 00:12:27.990
in Residence with us at LC Labs.

00:12:27.990 --> 00:12:29.650
And what you're seeing
here is one

00:12:29.650 --> 00:12:32.690
of our photograph
collections extrapolated

00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:34.010
into color palettes.

00:12:34.010 --> 00:12:38.050
So each of these swatches of
color represents one item.

00:12:38.050 --> 00:12:39.750
And if you were to click
on it you'd jump back

00:12:39.750 --> 00:12:43.280
to our lc.gov collection and
be able to explore that item.

00:12:43.280 --> 00:12:46.700
And she did visualize the
baseball card collection,

00:12:46.700 --> 00:12:48.620
so if you're curious
about seeing that,

00:12:48.620 --> 00:12:52.580
I would suggest you go onto
our Experiments site and look

00:12:52.580 --> 00:12:56.170
at the baseball one because
it's incredibly beautiful

00:12:56.170 --> 00:12:57.470
and colorful.

