00:43:50.990 --> 00:43:54.650
that we've done,
a text analyzer.

00:43:54.650 --> 00:43:58.070
As I said, academic
research can be daunting

00:43:58.070 --> 00:44:01.180
and challenging and
in various ways.

00:44:01.180 --> 00:44:05.220
And text analyzer we
envisioned as a different way

00:44:05.220 --> 00:44:08.550
of doing research to
overcome some of the hurdles.

00:44:08.550 --> 00:44:11.700
So text analyzer -- so for
those of you who aren't familiar

00:44:11.700 --> 00:44:14.600
with it, academic
research is often done

00:44:14.600 --> 00:44:16.650
through either citation mining,

00:44:16.650 --> 00:44:20.770
meaning you follow bibliography
one to the next to the next,

00:44:20.770 --> 00:44:23.760
or by keyword search like
you would do in Google,

00:44:23.760 --> 00:44:25.800
but in an academic database

00:44:25.800 --> 00:44:29.750
or in something called
Google Scholar.

00:44:29.750 --> 00:44:32.430
But those keywords and all
that can be challenging

00:44:32.430 --> 00:44:36.250
to a new student and if you're
doing the citation mining,

00:44:36.250 --> 00:44:39.880
you can get stuck in a
particular, in a silo.

00:44:39.880 --> 00:44:43.280
So what text analyzer does
is it changes that by instead

00:44:43.280 --> 00:44:46.530
of searching with words,
you search with a document.

00:44:46.530 --> 00:44:49.450
So if you've either found an
article that is already perfect

00:44:49.450 --> 00:44:51.230
and about what you're
writing about,

00:44:51.230 --> 00:44:53.080
or if you've written
the first draft

00:44:53.080 --> 00:44:55.960
of your paper, you
can upload it.

00:44:55.960 --> 00:44:59.210
So if we can drag the
sample document over.

00:44:59.210 --> 00:45:00.950
You just drag and drop it over,

00:45:00.950 --> 00:45:03.990
and what it does is it reads
the document and it figures

00:45:03.990 --> 00:45:05.670
out what the document is about.

00:45:05.670 --> 00:45:08.180
And it does that not just
by looking at the words,

00:45:08.180 --> 00:45:09.670
but the implied words.

00:45:09.670 --> 00:45:12.920
It uses a technology called
Natural Language Processing

00:45:12.920 --> 00:45:19.030
and topic models to figure out
the implied words in addition

00:45:19.030 --> 00:45:20.880
to the explicitly
mentioned ones.

00:45:20.880 --> 00:45:24.640
It calls attention to those
and tells you what it found,

00:45:24.640 --> 00:45:28.840
suggests another selection of
them in case there are some

00:45:28.840 --> 00:45:32.540
that are really important to
you, and then gives you articles

00:45:32.540 --> 00:45:35.930
in JSTOR, articles in book
chapters in JSTOR that are

00:45:35.930 --> 00:45:37.480
about the same materials.

00:45:37.480 --> 00:45:39.660
You can then, you
know, adjust the --

00:45:39.660 --> 00:45:43.720
we call it the equalizer at
the top which is a metaphor

00:45:43.720 --> 00:45:45.460
that probably nobody
gets anymore [laughter].

00:45:45.460 --> 00:45:50.750
You can add new terms and then,

00:45:50.750 --> 00:45:54.000
when you find the articles you
want, you can download this.

00:45:54.000 --> 00:45:56.610
This actually just won an
award a couple of weeks ago,

00:45:56.610 --> 00:45:58.730
which we're really
proud about, proud of.

